Wash and dry all produce. Preheat oven to 400 degrees. Bring @water{4%cups}, @diced tomatoes{2%boxes}, and @chicken stock concentrate{1} to a low simmer in a #small pot{}. Halve, peel, and dice @yellow onion{1}(peeled and diced).

Heat a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%teaspoon} in a large #ovenproof pan{} over medium heat (you'll need a lid later). Add onions, @Italian pork sausage{18%ounce}, and @garlic powder{2%teaspoon}. Break up meat into small pieces until sausage is browned and onion is softened, ~{5-6%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Add @Arborio rice{1.5%cup} and toss to combine until translucent, ~{1-2%minutes}. Add 4 cups warm tomato stock mixture. Cover and bake until rice is al dente, ~{18-20%minutes}.

> Hint: Transfer to a #baking dish{} if you don't have an ovenproof pan.

Prep the remaining ingredients: Finely chop @parsley{1/4%ounce}(finely chopped). Cut @zucchini{2}(cut into 1/2-inch cubes) into ½-inch cubes. Take risotto out of oven, stir in zucchini, and continue baking for remaining time.

Finish the risotto: Once rice is al dente, place pan back on stove over low heat. Stir in about 1 cup tomato stock mixture until a loose sauce forms. Add @Parmesan cheese{1/2%cup} and @butter{1%tablespoon}. Season generously with salt and pepper.

Serve: Finish with a sprinkle of parsley and enjoy!